</mxCell></object><object label="Animals matter a lot&lt;br&gt;(RP welfare ranges)&lt;br&gt;[1+2+3+4+5]&lt;br&gt;→ AI safety (Redwood Research)&lt;br&gt;(Bob Fischer, Brian Tomasik)" tooltip="&lt;b&gt;parochial + far_away_humans + animals_somewhat + future_humans_matter_with_discounting + no_discounting_future_humans + animals_matter_a_lot&lt;/b&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;Replace the neuron-count proxy with Rethink Priorities&#x27; welfare-range estimates (Fischer et al.) and count invertebrates — shrimp, insects, and the ~10^19 soil animals. Under RP medians a chicken&#x27;s welfare range is a third of a human&#x27;s, not a fiftieth, and wild/soil invertebrates carry significant aggregate (nematode) weight, so invertebrate work dominates. || Chain: 0 parochial → 1 far_away_humans → 2 animals_somewhat → 3 future_humans_matter_with_discounting → 4 no_discounting_future_humans → 5 animals_matter_a_lot" link="https://www.squiggle-language.com/playground#code=eJylVmFz4jYQ%2FSs7mXZKKCHGJL2GDh8IIZfMcb0MSXvTCRki7DVWI0seSY7D5fLfu7IhQDBtZuovGO%2Fq7e5b6Wmf90KMWCZsX4W419k7PIRutws3mnEJVkGg2bc5veQSxpnvtY4gV1qEjxxzyFsTf9KeHE2OoWasSuF43y0eSwLpGZMlqeVKQhATVgc8SJlWQcyZcFCtEx9aEDE9YTmbT%2BIsYdIsDT4wyRMmzMSoBPOY2aWlDVFmM42LBZOEWYt6knMbT0JuApVJy%2BVs6X4EUq1%2Fn2ysXnodv4ZbwLGJULaoY8CCGNiqGG6AwdXcxvQecYFANK3M5hCsS5aFoWmARuKWSzSgdAGm8YA4YAlSDG7ou42xpOcnQ3XJoMD4DQKVpMq4Ml4daK0MkRDpEzcFmrFMhkwoiZBQ80QT7l97M3i8d6m65fiUYmBp4SMTGYKKCoRVG5sF2CkaC9NsDpkL4xYaXC%2BsA71LMCxCO4faCMNcqRBG5MR0EO%2BXGB8Hvw9GvZvBGUznMEOJmllspvPlzsGQ2w2y6mRsUIdsmZLjk5AKrDOuKWvAKHI%2FRDa6Rig9I6ZSTc3Sc5hSiIgHnN4bcDo4%2FzIaEBOaiQIhRz6LXc%2BJF6HcXo75fdk%2FoWZSaWo4nHg%2FQv8SakpT1QcqOkjYTHKbhQinX24GfVeZUVn6idsgRnnGxPwK9R8mhC48jyVAiioVeIEixfDV4jW9YxfQax47nxyFmCJl8pEa6SBKF69V%2Bngt51TsUNQRC2zGxCmTD38W%2FXKu7R2R6hXQdai14GAX3P5YvozlLNwoxOXiHS2S8fyxZEm05dBeVOT5lC7jyZbDshqfarax2LC3mr6zHn0gNvN00%2BR7nrN9OKIkxjLnIpxmM7Pp80vp86tf%2BDAhIgwretGbaR6QlmW0B%2FrMMmO1SmMkrz5K%2Brokvr1IteiO4I9ortljweqZEoLpy2htdbmmyN93%2FmEZd8gjZ2p7ReQ%2Bf%2BSCf2Nu