lor=#4a2a78;fontColor=#201040;" vertex="1" parent="1"><mxGeometry x="0" y="1195" width="200" height="108" as="geometry"/></mxCell></object><object label="Living in&lt;br&gt;a simulation&lt;br&gt;[1+2+3+4+5+9]&lt;br&gt;→ Shrimp Welfare Project&lt;br&gt;(Nick Bostrom)" tooltip="&lt;b&gt;parochial + far_away_humans + animals_somewhat + future_humans_matter_with_discounting + no_discounting_future_humans + animals_matter_a_lot + living_in_simulation&lt;/b&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;If most observers like us are simulated, the astronomical future that justified x-risk work probably gets switched off long before it happens. The same expected-value reasoning that bought astronomical stakes now attenuates them: future-facing value is multiplied by the probability the simulation keeps running, and the ranking slides back toward the present. || Chain: 0 parochial → 1 far_away_humans → 2 animals_somewhat → 3 future_humans_matter_with_discounting → 4 no_discounting_future_humans → 5 animals_matter_a_lot → 9 living_in_simulation" link="https://www.squiggle-language.com/playground#code=eJylVmFT4zYQ%2FSs7TDsNKQTHgV5JJx9CCAdzuR4TaG86hDGKvY5VZMkjyZgcx3%2Fvyk4gIU7LTP0ljrX7dvet9klPOxHGLBd2oCLc6e4cHECv14NrzbgEqyDU7NucXgoJk9z32odQKC2iB44FFO3ADzrBYXAUHEPDWJXB8a5zn0iC6RuTp5nlSkKYEFoXPMiYVmHCmXBg7WMf2hAzHbCCzYMkT5k0ywUfmOQpEyYwKsUiYXa50oE4t7nGhUOQMmtRBwW3SRBxE6pcWi5nS%2FNDkGr1e7DmvbQ6egm3gGOBUC8hj0HwB%2BfLZWB4mgvmyiqrHLIwAfZaKjfA4HJuE3qPuUAgGl%2BXzQFYVwqLIrMHGol7LtGA0iWYxn1iiKVIGXBD322CFXk%2FGapahiXGbxCqNFPGFfliQL4yQkKkT9yUaMYyGTGhJEJKzRUtuHvp3fDhzqXq3PExw9CS4wMTOYKKS4TXNrdKsBM0Fqb5HHIXxjkaXC2sC1eJ5mkGX1FQSxEutfqbcCvvj8Pfh%2BP%2B9fAUpnOYoUTNLLay%2BXJPYcTtGk1NWtyjztkqGcckIZVYp1wTLmAcux%2BiGV0LlJ4RRxmlwPQcphQi5iGn9z04GZ59GQ%2BJA81EiVAgnyVuLxAjQrldnvC7qnNCzaTStBHg2PsRBhfQUJrq3Vfxfspmkts8Qjj5cj0c7FI%2BRuXZJ27DBOUpE%2FNL1H%2BYCHrwNJEAGapM4DmKDKOXFa%2FlHbmAXuvI2RQoxBQpk4%2FUQgdRmXjtysZrO6Ny56KOWWhzJk6YvP%2Bz7JQz7WyJ1KyBbkKjDfvb4HYn8nkiZ9FaIS4X73CRjOdPJEvjDYPOoiLPp3QZTzcMltX4VLNNxNp6u%2BW71cMPxGaRrS%2F5nufWPhxSEhNZcBFN85lZt%2FmlsvnVL22YEDFGNb3ozzQPSeVy2gMDZpmxWmUJktUAJX1dEt9ZpFp2h4YezRV7KFk9VUIwfRGveFc%2BZf6%2Bs4%2BquCMeu6WOV0YekHII%2Fq1UjKGMXEMIVm7ALPdF2XKa%2FvurhMZojKlaje9Kxv12WTO9eMfOulI0V7Xp2yvL7h1k23t9SmvvzfNOXpr%2FTUNzrfKf34f6HmKa%2F0JEs6bscguTBhZK1WyCxzGBjTHKw01COwtC2%2F7%2FI7Q%2BxtZcqyPkpjjtj%2F4CYlg7Hc5IX3%2B47a7qWrSmeZani7PhVdNCRYukeMTvG%2F0md%2FbmKIYst8ZJJ3f6TEejOzd6cOMqeAIacuzCZGekQtJBp3FwX4ncZGcPiuiF2C6kyGSjVgV3qeg2PO%2BtQ7oOV%2Fot5vVgqwK0HYMOGQHuvkHlaG7n0Oh%2FPtutR1yTrHrI%2FsVnOIDBAmsorcaMzlPMtUl4tgV2VejqYa%2BpQ%2BfumoEwQjbLsR5pTRIdEsl6x99Aqz9ft7RkVUorSK%2BzmeBXklS6oBjCMdBIqlQzOulpI0VothC6KcSLCDXEjkZnw9MtBL7R6gqkrjlgWIyuyeNqtGFMlw%2Bmw2RLghsKsAp966ZO06nnrk89GHFjWxpp9Aw2yj9GaXsyb1RTsQdP3x%2B%2Fw2NrJcrzLp2VU3cf6sEC6Ma7XQzzde2N6vr84up1IrtQ3mc5kT5dXqto1jllYWgeVy5pFMFZrEafyJ3nfwApt%2Fte" id="w1_2_3_4_5_9"><mxCell style="rounded=1;whiteSpace=wrap;html=1;fontSize=11;fillColor=#eeb3b3;strokeColor=#c0392b;fontColor=#5a1410;" vertex="1" parent="1"><mxGeometry x="1617" y="717" width="200" height="108" as="geometry"/></mxCell></object><object label="Person-affecting&lt;br&gt;view&lt;br&gt;[1+2+3+4+5+9+10]&lt;br&gt;→ Shrimp Welfare Project&lt;br&gt;(Jan Narveson, Melinda Roberts)" tooltip="&lt;b&gt;parochial + far_away_humans + animals_somewhat + future_humans_matter_with_discounting + no_discounting_future_humans + animals_matter_a_lot + living_in_simulation + person_affecting_view&lt;/b&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;Person-affecting population ethics: making happy people is neutral, so the astronomical case for x-risk reduction — which rests on the sheer number of extra future lives saved from extinction — loses almost all its force. Only the harm to people who exist regardless still counts. This is the standard premise longtermism&#x27;s critics deny (discussed as the key objection in Greaves &amp; MacAskill&#x27;s &#x27;The Case for Strong Longtermism&#x27;). It requires no_discounting_future_humans, the astronomical-stakes move it pushes back on. || Chain: 0 parochial → 1 far_away_humans → 2 animals_somewhat → 3 future_humans_matter_with_discounting → 4 no_discounting_future_humans → 5 animals_matter_a_lot → 9 living_in_simulation → 10 person_affecting_view" link="https://www.squiggle-language.com/playground#code=eJylVmFv2zYQ%2FSuHYMMcL3EkOWkXD%2F7gOE4bzF0LJ1sxxIVKSyeLC0UKJBXFTfPfd5TsxI7lLcD8SSaP7%2B7e8d7xYS%2FGhBXCDlWMe729oyPo9%2FtwrRmXYBVEmn1b0EcpYVoEnn8MpdIivuNYQumHQdgNj8OT8DT0PWgZq3LwvX0HMZUENTCmyHLLlYQoJcQeeJAzraKUM%2BEA%2FdMAfEiYDlnJFmFaZEya1UYATPKMCRMalWGZMrva6UJS2ELj8kCYMWtRhyW3aRhzE6lCWi7nK%2FNjkGp9Pdw4vbI6eXK3hGOhUE8uT0HwO3eWy9DwrBCsSmuVA%2BWF2igZsiTBqHLiOKpYGLEoBfZMBTfA4NPCpvSdcIFAVD9vmyOwLlUWx%2BYANFJ9uEQDSldgGg%2BJQZYhRcgNrdsUa3J%2FMsSKjCqMXyFSWa6MI%2BHJgM7KGAmRlrip0IxlMmZCSYSMLoDowNen%2Bo7uvrpQ3XG8zykpOnjHRIGgkgrh%2BSp0KrAzNBZmxQIK58YdNLieWA%2BuUs2zHD6joJIjfNLqb8KtT78b%2FT6aDK5H5zBbwBwlamaxky9W9w5jbjdoatPmAVXW1sE4JgmpwjrnmnABq1oA0YyuBErPiaOcQmB6ATNykfCI0%2FcBnI0uPk5GxIFmokIokc9TV0ZiRCjXCSn%2FWldOqLlUmi4KnHo%2FwvASWkpTvocqOczYXHJbxAhnH69Hw32Kx6gi%2F43bKEV5zsTiE%2Bo%2FTAx9eJhKoDujcoHvUeQYP%2B14He%2FEOfQ6J86mRCFmSJG8oxI6iNrE82sbz3dG1c1GnbDIFkycMXn7Z1UpZ9rd4andAN2Glg%2BHu%2BD2p%2FJxKufxRiIuFu94GYwXTCXLki2D7jIjL6BwGc%2B2DFbZBJSzTcXGvt8J3O7xW2KzzDe3As9ze2%2BPKYipLLmIZ8XcbNq8qW1%2BCSobJkSCcUMtBnPNI1LCgu7AkFlmrFZ5imQ1REmrK%2BK7y1Cr6pAooLlidxWr50oIpi%2BTtdP1mSr%2BwNnHtd8xT9xW16s8D0lZBP9WKcpIxq4gBCu3YFb3oio5df%2FtVUptNMFMrft3KeOhX%2BVMH96ps64Vz2VtBvbKslsH6XvPv8rae%2FF7JS%2Ft%2F6ahvZH5z69DfQ0x7X8hot2QdnWFSQNLpRouwf2EwCYYF9E2od0loX7w%2Fwht9rEz1nqE3JTng%2FFfQAxrp8M0bOCHL711XYs3NM%2FybDkbnjUtUrRJikf8vtBvOs5ejGrIC2ucdHKnzzQ63dzow43L4AGoybEH072xikgHncbBbS1y070DKOMnYnuQIZOtRhXcp6R9eDzYhHQVrvVbLJrB1gVoNwYNGQHuQULpaG4X0Bp8uNhvRtyQrGbIweUHOILhEmskrcac5ikW2qQ83wG7LnTNsNdUoffuGYIwRjYvsBlpQxIdEsl6N9hCa56vO0qyLqU1pNfdDvAzSSo9UAzhGGildag5TXq6SDGaHYRuC%2FHSQwOx4%2FHF6HwHgS%2B02oF0SdLeNJQHDEvQlXlSNzdM6PnBdJTuCHFLAzbBv7jO0zT53BOqD2NubEcjtZ%2FBVvXHKG3PFq26Mw7g4fv9d7jvrPl53Kd5OXNvoj4sgW68L8uGvm58VV2%2Fv7x67soeVG9eTsTPVk8r6ndOURjqybWHGnlwFuvep3Lv8R9lSQik" id="w1_2_3_4_5_9_10"><mxCell style="rounded=1;whiteSpace=wrap;html=1;fontSize=11;fillColor=#d7c6e6;strokeColor=#6a3fa0;fontColor=#2c1650;" vertex="1" parent="1"><mxGeometry x="1922" y="956" width="251" height="108" as="geometry"/></mxCell></object><object label="Count soil animals&lt;br&gt;(~10^19 nematodes)&lt;br&gt;[1+2+3+4+5+9+10+11]&lt;br&gt;→ Shrimp Welfare Project&lt;br&gt;(Vasco Grilo)" tooltip="&lt;b&gt;parochial + far_away_humans + animals_somewhat + future_humans_matter_with_discounting + no_discounting_future_humans + animals_matter_a_lot + living_in_simulation + person_affecting_view + soil_animals&lt;/b&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;Grilo&#x27;s soil-animal accounting: ~10^19 soil nematodes, mites and springtails dominate the welfare effects of almost anything. Global-health charities raise food demand and cropland (~137 m^2-yr/$ for GiveWell top charities, ~1.11 kQALY/$ of soil-animal welfare change); with soil lives net-negative, the arithmetic makes GiveWell&#x27;s top charities net-harmful. Only enters once invertebrates already count, so it requires animals_matter_a_lot. || Chain: 0 parochial → 1 far_away_humans → 2 animals_somewhat → 3 future_humans_matter_with_discounting → 4 no_discounting_future_humans → 5 animals_matter_a_lot → 9 living_in_simulation → 10 person_affecting_view → 11 soil_animals" link="https://www.squiggle-language.com/playground#code=eJylVmFz2kYQ%2FSs7nnaKqY0lgW2gwweMSeIpaTLYbacTMsohrdDVpzvN3cmYOP7v3ZPAgIE2M%2FUnrN17u%2Ft27%2B09HcWYsELYgYrxqHt0dga9Xg%2FuNOMSrIJIs68L%2BjGXMCkCz2%2FBXGkRP3Ccw9wPg7AZtsLzsBP6Xuj7UDNW5eD7xw5lIgmtb0yR5ZYrCVFKoF3wIGdaRSlnwmH6nQB8SJgO2ZwtwrTImDQrQwBM8owJExqV4TxldmVpQlLYQuPyQJgxa1GHc27TMOYmUoW0XM5W7i2QavN7uHV65XX%2BEm4Jx0KhXkJ2QPAHd5bL0PCsEKwsa1UD1YXaKBmyJMGoDFLStLL7YBQX4TJCSc6QRSmwNUPcAIOPC5vS74QLBGrC2mzOwDoGWBybE9BIneMSDShdgmk8JWJZhpQ4N%2FTdplhx%2FpMhsmRUYvwCkcpyZRw3Lw50VsZIiPSJV6kZy2TMhJIIGY2GaMCXl84PH764VN1xfMypVjr4wESBoJISYT0kjRLsCo2FabGAwoVxBw1uFtaF21TzLIc%2FUdAkIHzU6m%2FCrU6%2FHf42HPfv